reviews.review_text:
Let it Pour! The most significant audience recording to emerge on archive in many ages.  I have never seen or heard of an audience source of this show, and for what it is, a front of board in the rain, the sound is spectacular (particularly if you grew up with audience tapes and few sbds like me).

Perhaps the highlight is the feeling of anticipation that emerges within the crowd during the waning minutes of Foolish Heart, when the band starts heavily teasing the Dark Star groove.  One of those moments that sends a chill through the spine.

Other notables are the incredibly sublime Touch of Grey which takes to the skies, and the first un-cut recording of The Weight.  Hearing the crowd sing along with their hearts fully invested in the moment is a wonderful sound, a wonderful sound indeed.
Down and dirty This show is down and dirty, The grunge like start to touch of grey, not really a fan of the song. Having seen it 70 times is a lot but this one is on the money
OK, EVERYONE knows about this show So I won't bother writing a long review.  It's an all-timer.  The sound on this audience is crystal clear.  An easy 5 stars.
